Calculator Using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript

This project is a fully functional calculator built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. It provides a simple and user-friendly interface for performing basic arithmetic operations such as addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division. HTML is used to create the calculator structure, CSS is used to design a modern and responsive user interface, and JavaScript handles all calculation logic and user interactions.

The project demonstrates fundamental web development concepts, including DOM manipulation, event handling, responsive design, and JavaScript functions. It is an excellent beginner-friendly project for understanding how HTML, CSS, and JavaScript work together to create interactive web applications.
